body:
I made a few changes in this one so here's a summary of what I did:

* Removed some code that was out of context, now each example should contain only what's relevant (there were some event listeners or chat commands that were probably added as a test)
* Added a description on top of each file so it's clear what each example does
* Changed the way chat commands are parsed and separated most reactions to commands in smaller  functions so it's easier to see what each command does without reading all the code
* Added comments explaining the syntax of the most complicated commands
* Reordered some code so functions are easier to find
* Separated a few other functions and statements so each example is easier to follow
* Fixed a few style inconsistencies

I tested every example manually to check that they were working and everything seems to be fine.

I think there are a few other optimizations that can be done, especially since there's some repetitive code that can be put in a reusable functions instead and some code that could be shared between examples but I didn't want to do too much at once. If everything looks good to you I might do that before merging.

commit.message: Use stricter regex patterns for chat commands
Show experience level in chests example
Simplify and rename listInventory to make it consistent across examples
Use Item.fromNotch and remove duplicate function from chatterbox example
Add check in jumper example to prevent crash when no entities are found
Use the same findBlock in all examples, remove findBed, findChest and findFurnace
